30.08	The_Canon_of_Medicine	The Canon of Medicine	The Canon of Medicine (Arabic: ‎)(Persian: ‎) (originally written in Arabic language) is an encyclopedia of medicine in five books compiled by Ibn Sīnā (Avicenna) and completed in 1025. It presents a clear and organized summary of all the medical knowledge of the time. Although originally written in Arabic language, the book was later translated into a number of other languages, including Latin, Chinese, Hebrew, German, French, and English with lots of commentaries. The Canon is considered one of the most famous books in the history of medicine.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/The_Canon_of_Medicine.jpg/220px-The_Canon_of_Medicine.jpg
